## 13.5 Spawn Grids and Patterns

Spawning one-by-one is tedious. **`scene/spawn-many`** and **`scene/grid`** spawn prefabs in bulk.

### Example 13.9: A Grid of Wanderers

```scheme
(prefab/define 'wanderer
  (lambda (x y sprite speed radius)
    (let ([id (world/spawn x y 'wanderer)])
      (entity/sprite! id sprite)
      (ai/wander id radius 1.0)
      (entity/max-speed! id speed)
      id)))

(define (setup)
  (world/reset!)
  (scene/grid 'wanderer 4.0 4.0 4 3 4.0 4.0
              'blossom-1 0.3 0.5)
  0)

(big-bang (setup)
  [on-tick (lambda (n)
             (world/step)
             (+ n 1))]
  [stop-when (lambda (n) (>= n 200))])
```

**`(scene/grid prefab x0 y0 cols rows dx dy ...args)`**:
- Spawns `(* cols rows)` instances of `prefab`.
- Top-left at `(x0, y0)`, spaced `dx` apart horizontally, `dy` vertically.
- Each gets `...args` as remaining parameters.

Here: 4 columns, 3 rows, spacing 4.0×4.0 → 12 wanderers in a grid.

[VISUAL: A 4×3 grid of blossom-1 sprites, all wandering within their local neighborhoods.]

<!-- BUILD: wire Example 13.9 runnable; implement scene/grid as a loop over prefab/spawn. -->

---

### Example 13.10: Varied Grid

Pass a list of sprites instead of a single one; `scene/grid` cycles through them.

```scheme
(define (setup)
  (world/reset!)
  (scene/grid 'wanderer 4.0 4.0 4 3 4.0 4.0
              (list 'blossom-1 'blossom-5 'blossom-9)
              0.3 0.5)
  0)

(big-bang (setup)
  [on-tick (lambda (n)
             (world/step)
             (+ n 1))]
  [stop-when (lambda (n) (>= n 200))])
```

**Result:** First row: blossom-1, blossom-5, blossom-9, blossom-1. Second row: blossom-5, blossom-9, blossom-1, blossom-5. Third row: blossom-9, blossom-1, blossom-5, blossom-9.

[VISUAL: A 4×3 grid, flowers cycling through three types.]

<!-- BUILD: wire Example 13.10 runnable; ensure scene/grid accepts lists for cycled params. -->

