## 13.6 Putting It Together: The Garden Scene

We have all the pieces. Now compose them.

**The scenario:**
- A 3×3 grid of flowers, swaying (Chapter 3's `part/sway`).
- A flock of 8 wanderers (Chapter 10's `ai/wander`).
- Two seekers (Chapter 10's `ai/seek`) that chase the nearest wanderer.
- A particle emitter raining pollen (Chapter 7).
- A camera that follows the centroid of the seekers (Chapter 14 preview: `world/camera-follow!`).

### Prefabs

```scheme
(prefab/define 'flower
  (lambda (x y)
    (let ([id (world/spawn x y 'flower)])
      (entity/sprite! id 'blossom-3)
      (entity/set! id 'sway-phase (world/hash id))
      id)))

(prefab/define 'wanderer
  (lambda (x y)
    (let ([id (world/spawn x y 'wanderer)])
      (entity/sprite! id 'blossom-1)
      (ai/wander id 0.8 1.0)
      (entity/max-speed! id 0.4)
      (entity/tag! id 'prey)
      id)))

(prefab/define 'seeker
  (lambda (x y)
    (let ([id (world/spawn x y 'seeker)])
      (entity/sprite! id 'blossom-7)
      (entity/max-speed! id 0.6)
      (entity/tag! id 'predator)
      id)))

(prefab/define 'emitter
  (lambda (x y)
    (let ([id (world/spawn x y 'emitter)])
      (entity/set! id 'emit-rate 3)
      (entity/set! id 'particle-life 180)
      id)))
```

### Scene Data

```scheme
(define garden
  '((prefabs
      (emitter 40.0 2.0))
    (world
      (gravity 0.0 0.02)
      (camera-bounds 0.0 0.0 80.0 24.0))))
```

We'll spawn flowers, wanderers, seekers in code (to use `scene/grid` and `scene/spawn-many`).

### Tick Logic

```scheme
(define (emit-particles id)
  (when (entity/alive? id)
    (let ([rate (entity/get id 'emit-rate)]
          [life (entity/get id 'particle-life)]
          [pos (entity/pos id)]
          [x (car pos)]
          [y (cadr pos)])
      (let loop ([i 0])
        (when (< i rate)
          (let ([pid (world/spawn x y 'particle)])
            (entity/set-vel! pid (* 0.15 (- (world/hash (+ i (* 1000 (world/frame)))) 0.5)) 0.0)
            (entity/set! pid 'life life))
          (loop (+ i 1)))))))

(define (tick-particles)
  (world/each
    (lambda (id)
      (when (eq? (entity/kind id) 'particle)
        (let ([life (entity/get id 'life)])
          (if (<= life 0)
              (entity/despawn! id)
              (entity/set! id 'life (- life 1))))))))

(define (sway-flowers)
  (world/each
    (lambda (id)
      (when (eq? (entity/kind id) 'flower)
        (let ([phase (entity/get id 'sway-phase)])
          (part/sway id 'stem (* 8.0 (dsin (+ phase (* 0.05 (world/frame)))))))))))

(define (seekers-chase)
  (world/each
    (lambda (id)
      (when (entity/tag! id 'predator)
        (let ([target (world/nearest id 'prey)])
          (when target
            (ai/seek id (entity/x target) (entity/y target))))))))

(define (camera-follow-seekers)
  (let ([predators (group/find 'predator)])
    (when (> (group/count predators) 0)
      (let ([cx 0.0]
            [cy 0.0]
            [n (group/count predators)])
        (group/each predators
          (lambda (id)
            (set! cx (+ cx (entity/x id)))
            (set! cy (+ cy (entity/y id)))))
        (world/camera-follow! (/ cx n) (/ cy n) 0.05)))))
```

*(Note: `set!` is a Scheme mutation primitive; we use it here for centroid accumulation. If your Scheme subset forbids `set!`, accumulate via recursion + cons instead.)*

### Setup and Loop

```scheme
(define (setup)
  (world/reset!)
  (scene/load garden)
  ;; Spawn flowers in a 3×3 grid
  (scene/grid 'flower 8.0 8.0 3 3 8.0 4.0)
  ;; Spawn 8 wanderers scattered
  (scene/spawn-many 'wanderer
    (list 12.0 4.0)
    (list 20.0 8.0)
    (list 28.0 6.0)
    (list 36.0 10.0)
    (list 44.0 5.0)
    (list 52.0 12.0)
    (list 60.0 7.0)
    (list 68.0 9.0))
  ;; Spawn 2 seekers
  (prefab/spawn 'seeker 8.0 16.0)
  (prefab/spawn 'seeker 72.0 16.0)
  0)

(big-bang (setup)
  [on-tick (lambda (n)
             (world/each
               (lambda (id)
                 (when (eq? (entity/kind id) 'emitter)
                   (emit-particles id))))
             (tick-particles)
             (sway-flowers)
             (seekers-chase)
             (camera-follow-seekers)
             (world/step)
             (+ n 1))]
  [stop-when (lambda (n) (>= n 600))])
```

[VISUAL: A wide canvas. Three columns of flowers swaying in the lower-left. Eight small blossoms wandering across the middle. Two larger blossoms (seekers) chasing the nearest wanderer. Particles raining from top-center, drifting down. Camera pans smoothly to keep both seekers in frame.]

